cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CY, cs.SE 

The paper discusses the use of distributed ledgers and blockchain technology in transactive microgrids, which involves communication and transactional anonymity. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Cybersecurity (cs.CY), and Software Engineering (cs.SE). Among these categories, cs.CR is the most likely as the paper focuses on privacy preservation and transactional integrity, which are key concerns in cryptography and security. The other categories are also relevant as they involve distributed systems, control, and software engineering, which are all relevant to the design and implementation of transactive microgrids.
